  "text": "There are several advantages to this kind of system. 1-dimensional concentration profiles of almost arbitrary complexity can be set up with relative ease. Innovations to the basic design of these assays also allow rapid temporal control of gradient shape, enabling the quantitative study of both spatial and temporal components of chemotaxis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Similarly, cells can easily be exposed to additional pharmacological reagents.",
